{{zh-hanzi}}

# [[piece]]; [[item]]; [[individual]]
#: {{zh-x|個{gè}人|an individual; personal}}
#: {{zh-x|個{gè}體|individuality}}
# [[size]]; [[height]]
#: {{zh-x|個{gè}子{zi}|height; stature}}
#: {{zh-x|個{gè}兒{r}|size}}
# [[separate]]; [[respective]]; [[separately]]; [[individually]]
#: {{zh-x|個{gè}別|individual; separate; some; a couple of}}
# [[single]]; [[alone]]
# {{lb|zh|dialectal Hakka|dialectal Min|dialectal Wu}} [[one]]
# {{n-g|The generic classifier for people or for things lacking specific classifiers.}}
#* {{zh-x|一 個{gè} 人|one person}}
#* {{zh-x|每 個{gè} 人|every person; everyone}}
#* {{zh-x|我 有 一 個{gè} 問題。|I have a question.}}
#* {{zh-x|兩{nn̄g} 個 人|two people|TW}}
#* {{zh-x|住 響 你 屋企 個 陳 先生 係 邊度 人 嚟 㗎？|Where is that Mr. Chan who lives at your house from?|C-GZ}}
# {{zh-classifier|[[hour]]s and [[month]]s}}
#* {{zh-x|一 個{gè} 鐘頭|one hour}}
#* {{zh-x|九 個{gè} 月|nine months}}
#* {{zh-x|三 個{kò} 月|three months|TW}}
# {{n-g|Alternative classifier, for nouns having specific classifiers. Often colloquial and regional. Usage varies greatly between different topolects.}}
#* {{zh-x|一 個{gè} 學校|one school}}
#* {{zh-x|一 個 井|a well|C-GZ}}
#* {{zh-x|一 個 房{fong4-2}|a room|C-GZ}}
# {{lb|zh|Cantonese}} {{zh-classifier|[[yuan]], [[dollar]]s, etc., used when followed by cents}}
#* {{zh-x|三 個 九 毫 九|three '''dollars''' and ninety-nine cents|C}}
#* {{zh-x|八 個 六|eight '''dollars''' and sixty cents|C}}
#* {{zh-x|個 半 十 隻 檸檬{mung4-1}|ten lemons for a '''dollar''' and a half|C}}
# {{lb|zh|Mandarin|colloquial}} {{n-g|Particle, placed between a verb and numbers, showing that the following numbers are approximate, not accurate.}}
#* {{zh-x|他 一下 跑 個{gè} 兩 三 公里 都 不在話下。|Running two or three kilometers in one go is a piece of cake for him.}}
#* {{zh-x|他們 倆 就 差{chà} 個{gè} 一 兩 歲。|The age difference between them is only about one or two years.}}
# {{lb|zh|Mandarin|Cantonese|colloquial}} {{n-g|Particle, placed between a verb and its object or complement, adding a sense of ease, swiftness and one-offness to the action.}}
#* {{zh-x|吃 個{gè} 飯，洗 個 澡，休息{xi} 休息{xi}|have a meal, take a shower and have some rest}}
#* {{zh-x|我們 昨天 見 了 個{gè} 面，聊 了 聊 近況。|We met yesterday, and chatted about how we've been recently.}}
# {{lb|zh|Mandarin|colloquial}} {{n-g|Particle used after {{zh-l|些}}.}}
#* {{zh-x|那些 個{gè} 年 的 事 現在 回憶 起來 還是 記憶猶新。|It feels like yesterday when I reminisce about those stories in the past.}}
# {{lb|zh|dialectal Mandarin}} {{n-g|Particle used in some time-related words.}}
#* {{zh-x|今兒{r}個|(''dialectal'') today}}
# {{lb|zh|literary|or|Wu|Xiang|Gan|dialectal Cantonese|dialectal|_|Min}} (= {{zh-l|*搿}}) [[this]]; [[that]]
#* {{zh-x|'''個''' 個 人|this person|SH}}
#* {{zh-x|個 隻 鴨子 勿 太 酥|This duck hasn't been cooked long enough for it to become tender.|SH}}
# {{lb|zh|Cantonese|Wu}} {{n-g|Word-initial particle, serving as the definite article.}}
#* {{zh-x|個 人 今朝 為啥 勿 來|Why hasn't that guy come today?|SH}}
# {{lb|zh|dialectal Cantonese|Hakka|Wu|Teochew|Hokkien}} {{n-g|Possessive particle. Equivalent to Mandarin {{zh-l|的|tr=de}}.}}
#: → {{zh-l|嘅|tr=ge3}} {{qualifier|Cantonese}}, {{zh-l|格|tr=kaq}} {{qualifier|Wu}}, {{zh-l|的|tr=ê}} {{qualifier|Min Nan}}
#* {{zh-x|我 個 小囡|my child|SH}}
#* {{zh-x|客家 個 精神|the Hakka spirit|H}}
# {{lb|zh|dialectal}} {{n-g|Sentence-final declarative, affirmative, or prohibitive particle. Equivalent to Mandarin {{zh-l|的|tr=de}}, {{zh-l|了}}.}}
#* {{zh-x|標語 勿 是 我 寫 個。|I didn't write that slogan.|SH}}
# {{lb|zh|often|dialectal}} {{n-g|Emphatic particle between a pronoun and a noun, usually to highlight some negative quality of the person.}}
#* {{zh-x|你 個{gè} 笨蛋！|You idiot!}}
#* {{zh-x|佢 個 人 好 懶。|He/she is such a sluggard.|C}}
